    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/swedish-style-lean-pork-meatballs-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-peas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) with your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a generous pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>then mix thoroughly with clean hands until fully combined, then shape into 6 <strong>meatballs </strong>per person</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min on each side or until browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/swedish-style-lean-pork-meatballs-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-peas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong>, your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and<strong> redcurrant jelly</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>sultanas</strong> to a bowl and cover with <strong>boiled water </strong>and set aside to soften</p><p>Once the meatballs have browned, transfer them to a plate (reserving the pan) and set aside, these will finish cooking in the sauce later</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/swedish-style-lean-pork-meatballs-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-peas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat, add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and stir until sandy (if your pan is looking dry add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong>)</p><p>Gradually whisk in the <strong>stock </strong>and cook for 2-3 min until slightly thickened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/swedish-style-lean-pork-meatballs-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-peas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sauce thickens, chop your<strong> dill</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add most of the<strong> chopped dill</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) to the thickened sauce</p><p>Return the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 12-15 min further until the meatballs are cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened to a gravy-like consistency \u2013 these are your <strong>lean</strong> <strong>pork Swedish-style meatballs & gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/swedish-style-lean-pork-meatballs-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-peas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Return the pot of drained <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat and add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Mash until smooth, then season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/swedish-style-lean-pork-meatballs-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-peas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p><p>Drain the <strong>soaked</strong> <strong>sultanas</strong>, discarding the soaking liquid</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/swedish-style-lean-pork-meatballs-with-sweet-potato-mash-and-peas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>lean</strong> <strong>pork</strong> <strong>Swedish-style meatballs & gravy</strong> with the <strong>mash </strong>and <strong>peas</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sultanas </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped dill</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
